<div id="this-page-explains-the-full-setup-needed-to-work-on-broodai"
><h1
  ><a href="#TOC"
    >This page explains the full setup needed to work on BroodAI</a
    ></h1
  ><div id="prerequisites"
  ><h2
    ><a href="#TOC"
      >Prerequisites</a
      ></h2
    ><div id="needed:"
    ><h3
      ><a href="#TOC"
	>Needed:</a
	></h3
      ><ul
      ><li
	>Windows (XP or Vista)</li
	><li
	>Visual Studio (Express 2008 at least)</li
	><li
	>BWAPI library + Chaoslauncher</li
	><li
	>GIT (version control)</li
	><li
	>Starcraft: Broodwar (latest patch)</li
	><li
	>Boost Library (currently 1.42)</li
	></ul
      ></div
    ><div id="optional:"
    ><h3
      ><a href="#TOC"
	>Optional:</a
	></h3
      ><ul
      ><li
	>Your favorite editor</li
	><li
	>Python (for cpplint.py and scrapper scripts)</li
	><li
	>Qt SDK (for debugger output)</li
	><li
	>ProBT (not used right now but soon for strategies)</li
	><li
	>Cygwin</li
	><li
	>Perl+Pandoc+make (to edit this wiki)</li
	></ul
      ></div
    ></div
  ><div id="walkthrough"
  ><h2
    ><a href="#TOC"
      >Walkthrough</a
      ></h2
    ><ol style="list-style-type: decimal;"
    ><li
      >Install VS (&gt;= Express 2008)</li
      ><li
      >Install Starcraft: Broodwar and patch</li
      ><li
      >Download BWAPI here: <a href="http://code.google.com/bwapi/"
	><code
	  >http://code.google.com/bwapi/</code
	  ></a
	> and install it all as said in the README (DLLs in /Windows/, injector DLL in chaoslauncher, bwapi-data in Starcraft/)</li
      ><li
      >In this folder (where BWAPI is, where you have include/ and lib/ for BWAPI), git clone git+ssh://inrialogin@scm.gforge.inria.fr//gitroot//broodai/broodai.git</li
      ><li
      >Open the .sln file of the cloned repository with VS</li
      ><li
      >Change the paths of include and linked library files in project properties for both Macro and Micro. If you have the right directory structure BWAPI/broodai/BroodAIProject.sln alongside BWAPI/include/ and BWAPI/lib/ you shouldn't have to change the paths for BWAPI lib.</li
      ><li
      >Build all in Release mode</li
      ><li
      >Change your Path variable in Windows (System Properties <span class="math"
	> → </span
	> Advanced) to contain Qt and stuff, example: <code
	>C:\Python26;C:\nant-0.86-beta1\bin;C:\Program Files\Parallels\Parallels Tools\Applications;%SystemRoot%\system32;%SystemRoot%;%SystemRoot%\System32\Wbem;C:\Program Files\Mercurial;C:\Program Files\Lua\5.1;C:\Program Files\Lua\5.1\clibs;C:\Program Files\TortoiseHg;C:\Program Files\QuickTime\QTSystem\;C:\Program Files\GtkSharp\2.12\bin;C:\Program Files\CMake 2.8\bin;C:\Program Files\TortoiseSVN\bin;C:\Program Files\CGAL-3.6\auxiliary\gmp\lib;C:\CGAL\CGAL-3.6\auxiliary\gmp\lib;C:\Python26\Scripts;C:\Program Files\software.jessies.org\terminator\Resources\terminator\bin\;C:\Qt\4.6.2\bin;C:\Qt\4.6.2\lib</code
	></li
      ><li
      >Launch chaosluncher and click &quot;Config&quot; for the injector, change the path for the one of the DLL you want to use (under broodai/Release/)</li
      ><li
      >Launch Starcraft and a corresponding map</li
      ><li
      >Profit</li
      ></ol
    ></div
  ></div
>

